neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood of San Miguel Iztapalapa is a quiet, baroque place with pre-Columbian and colonial customs where you can enjoy Mexican culture with the Spanish colonial mix framed by the Catholic religion, which is why patron saint festivals are celebrated throughout the year. And punctually from September 28 to October 9. Also during Holy Week the crucifixion of Jesus Christ is represented. Another attraction of the neighborhood is the trade of the Central de Abasto, the largest market in Latin America, a tourist attraction for Mexico to the world. From the neighborhood you can travel to any part of Mexico City by Metro public transport system.
